                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/316a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in Great Britain, France,
                            Russia, Italy, and Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d1fn3">The same, on the same date, to the Ambassadors in
                        Germany, Austria-Hungary, and Turkey, except that the second sentence
                        begins, “If inquiry made you may reply,” instead of “You may say” (File No.
                        763.72119/325a).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Press this morning publishes report that President will send second note to
                    powers in effort to advance peace movement. You may say that this report is
                    utterly false and without foundation and that the President has not in
                    contemplation sending a second note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
